<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-01-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="227" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-01-13"><hi rend="italic">January 13,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Conger acknowledges Department’s telegram of the 10th instant, and
                        requests instructions concerning indemnities, an approximate estimate of war
                        expenditures, and wishes as to revision of the treaties.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>